doc: /** * Collapse the given assign expression into the expression directly * following it, if possible. * * @param expr The expression that may be moved. * @param exprParent The parent of {@code expr}. * @param value The value of this expression, expressed as a node. Each * expression may have multiple values, so this function may be called * multiple times for the same expression. For example, * * a = true; * * is equal to the name "a" and the boolean "true". * @return Whether the expression was collapsed successfully. */

/**
   * Determines whether we know enough about the given value to be able
   * to collapse it into subsequent expressions.
   *
   * For example, we can collapse booleans and variable names:
   * <code>
   * x = 3; y = x; // y = x = 3;
   * a = true; b = true; // b = a = true;
   * <code>
   * But we won't try to collapse complex expressions.
   *
   * @param value The value node.
   * @param isLValue Whether it's on the left-hand side of an expr.
   */
